author: Samuel Osborne
title: South Sudan plane crash: At least 44 feared dead after passenger jet comes down in airport
text:
14:03 GMT Click to followThe Independent Online 
A passenger plane is reported to have crashed at an airport in Wau, South Sudan, killing all 44 people on board. 
The South Sudanese National Courier newspaper carried photos showing the burned-out wreck of the plane on the tarmac at Wau Airport. 
Local media said all those on board were feared dead. #WAU : Photos of Burned Out South Supreme Airlines Plane Which Crashed in Wau Today. #SSudan #SouthSudan pic.twitter.com/LHk27r9v6m
